• Single spaces and pairs of consecutive spaces are replaced with corresponding numbers of underscores, while sequences of 3 or more consecutive spaces are replaced with a single hyphen.

• The algorithm handles edge cases including spaces at the beginning, middle, and end of the string by processing accumulated spaces both during iteration and after the loop ends.

